# DiffusionBackend (infrastructure)

Platform abstraction for the text-to-image inference runtime, plus the supporting value/component
types. Not an ECS system — driven by DiffusionSystem (ADR 0008).

## DiffusionBackend
Abstract interface: `LoadCheckpoint(checkpoint, controlNet)` loads the session-resident model once,
`IsLoaded()` reports readiness, `Generate(params)` runs one denoising loop synchronously (on a worker
thread) and returns an RGB `pg::Image` (empty on failure). `Create()` selects the concrete backend by
the renderer-API switch, mirroring AudioDevice:
- **StableDiffusionCppBackend** (DirectX11 builds) — wraps stable-diffusion.cpp (CUDA). Compiled active
  only when PigeonLib is built with `-DPG_ENABLE_DIFFUSION=ON` (defines `PG_STABLE_DIFFUSION_ENABLED`);
  otherwise it is an inert no-op so a plain build links without the heavy runtime.
- **TestingDiffusionBackend** (Testing builds) — deterministic mock: records the loaded paths and the
  last job params, returns a solid mid-grey image of the requested size. Lets tests exercise the full
  request → generate → register path with no CUDA, model files, or real inference.

## DiffusionJobParams
The fully-resolved inputs of one generation handed to the backend: prompt/negative/seed, steps, CFG
scale, sampler name, width/height, clip skip, the LoRA set (path + weight), an optional img2img init
image + denoise strength, and an optional single ControlNet hint image + strength. Carries no ECS or
resource-map knowledge.

## Image
A CPU RGB8 image (row-major, 3 bytes/pixel): the common pixel container for ControlNet hints, img2img
inits, and generated results.

## DiffusionBackendSingletonComponent
Holds the session backend (`m_Backend`) and `m_LoadAttempted` (guards the one-time resident load).

## DiffusionJob / DiffusionJobSingletonComponent
DiffusionJob is the in-flight (or just-finished) generation: an atomic state
(pending/running/done/failed), the target texture UUID, the result image, and the worker thread (joined
on destruction). DiffusionJobSingletonComponent owns the single active job via shared_ptr (null when
idle); only one generation runs at a time.

## GenerateImageRequestOneFrameComponent
App-emitted (engine-typed) request: target texture UUID (caller-assigned, like an audio Voice Handle),
prompt/negative/seed, optional Generation Config overrides, LoRA refs (UUID + weight), and an optional
OpenPose ControlNet (skeleton UUID + strength + a 2D placement transform). Unset config fields fall back
to the engine defaults. Optionally composites the generated subject over a background image (resolved like
an Input Image): either chroma-keyed (auto-detected key colour + threshold) or, when
`m_CompositeWithSkeletonMask` is set, via the ControlNet skeleton's silhouette as a soft alpha mask (the
mask path takes precedence). The composite runs on the worker thread, off the frame loop.

## RasterizeOpenPoseHintRequestOneFrameComponent
App-emitted (engine-typed) request to rasterize an OpenPose Skeleton's canonical hint and register it
as a Generated Texture under a caller-assigned target UUID, so the pose can be shown on screen rather
than only fed internally to a ControlNet job (ADR 0011). Carries the skeleton UUID, the target texture
UUID, and an output size (0 => fall back to the Generation Config defaults). Handled synchronously by
DiffusionSystem — not a Diffusion Job.

## RegisterGeneratedTextureRequestOneFrameComponent
Emitted by DiffusionSystem on completion (and for a rasterized OpenPose hint); carries the generated
image + target UUID for ResourceManagerSystem (sole writer of the resource map) to register as a
texture. ResourceManagerSystem also retains the RGB pixels as an Input Image under the same UUID so a
later generation can re-feed the result (ADR 0011).
